                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 704.5467/2.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of Switzerland</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Swiss Legation</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1914-11-12">undated</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram received at the Legation on November 12, 1914, and copied
                    to the Secretary of State November 14, 1914.]</p>
                <p>Please ask the United States Government to kindly cable authorization to its
                    Embassy in Constantinople that United States representatives protect in the
                    Ottoman Empire such citizens of Switzerland as are asking for such protection.
                    This will mostly affect Swiss citizens previously under the protection of Powers
                    now at war with Turkey.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hoffman</hi>, <lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">President of Confederation.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
